the other hamstring muscles (pâ‰¤0.002).
SUMMARY: We highlight the heterogeneity of hamstring activation patterns in 
different tasks. Hip-extension exercise selectively activates the long 
hamstrings, and the Nordic exercise preferentially recruits the semitendinosus. 
These findings have implications for strategies to prevent hamstring injury as 
well as potentially for clinicians targeting specific hamstring components for 
treatment (mechanotherapy).

