Cystic fibrosis transmembrane conductance regulator (CFTR) modulators are 
clinically available personalized medicines approved for some individuals with 
cystic fibrosis (CF) to target the underlying defect of disease. This review 
summarizes strategies used to develop CFTR modulators as therapies that improve 
function and availability of CFTR protein. Lessons learned from dissemination of 
